content.description: The easiest of the v0s on the little boulder left of Lab Rats, and the cleanest. Start seated on the right arete, around the corner a bit, and climb straight up. Great big holds that are pretty solid. Very safe. A good warm up.
content.location: Right arete, slightly around the corner, on the small boulder left of the main Lab Rats boulder.

content.description: A solid little problem on the boulder to the left of Lab Rats. Sit start on jugs near the center of the boulder, and climb up and slightly right into the faint scoop.
content.location: On the small/medium boulder left of the main Lab Rats boulder

content.description: Sit start on the far left side of the tan and orange face.  Your right hand will be in a finger bucket and your left will be in a mediocre side pull.  Work up and right, then up and left, then top out a little right.  Big moves between decent holds.
content.location: The obvious line on the beautiful face of the Lab Rats boulder.

content.description: The counterpart to Pinky, and a decent climb, with the notable detractions of a loose flake near the top and a lot of dust/lichen marring the topout.
content.location: When you are facing Lab Rats on the main boulder, there is a small boulder to the left, and you are looking at the main face of this boulder. There are two v0s on this face, and The Brain is the right line on this face.

content.description: Same start as for Lab Rats, but head right after double hand slot crimp. Very long move up and right to slopey pinch just below the lip. Have fun!
content.location: Lab Rats (last boulder at the end of the trail)

content.description: Great boulder with a couple of classic lines.
